ia-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vfp1665702791667.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vfp1665702791667.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vfp1665702791667.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vfp1665702791667\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Structure Worksheet\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Define Structure worksheet to create development objects, organize them, and set their properties.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__section_w1995ab1b7b1_w1996ab1b7_w1997ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__section_w1998ab1b7b3_w1999ab1b7_w2000ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d949332e60\">\n                  \n Tools\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2162e1_d2163e1_d2164e1\">Resource Browser—choose templates and other objects to create a new sub-object in the current main development object.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2165e1_d2166e1_d2167e1\">Structure Editor—shows the main development object and its sub-objects, as well as selected properties, as a tree. You can edit properties of the selected object here, or in the Properties Inspector.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2168e1_d2169e1_d2170e1\">Properties Inspector—shows the properties of the object selected in the Structure Editor, and enables you to edit them.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__section_w2001ab1b7b5_w2002ab1b7_w2003ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d949332e78\">\n                  \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2171e1_d2172e1_d2173e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"okr1665702619654.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/okr1665702619654.html\" title=\"New development objects may be created using templates and modeled objects. For main development objects, such as components and entities, it is also possible to create new object by duplicating an existing object.\">Create a New Development Object</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2174e1_d2175e1_d2176e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flj1690357335479.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flj1690357335479.html\" title=\"You can select templates, modeled objects, and code snippets in the Resource Browser and add them to current object. You can drag and drop objects, or use the context menu.\">Add Objects from the Resource Browser</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2177e1_d2178e1_d2179e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zum1665702619077.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zum1665702619077.html\" title=\"You can rename an object in-line in the Structure Editor, or in the Properties Inspector.\">Rename a Development Object</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2180e1_d2181e1_d2182e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xui1665702780196.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xui1665702780196.html\" title=\"You can edit object properties using the Properties Inspector.\">Edit Object Properties</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2183e1_d2184e1_d2185e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wvb1665702780266.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvb1665702780266.html\" title=\"Use the Property Inspector to set a property on multiple subobjects to the same value. This can be useful, for example, if you want to have several fields use the same data type or same widget type.\">Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vfp1665702791667__li_d2186e1_d2187e1_d2188e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kdb1665702780441.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdb1665702780441.html\" title=\"You can resize the width of columns by clicking the triangle in column header, and setting the desired width.\">Resize Columns</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Using the Uniface IDE</a><p>Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with Development Objects</a><p>Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tfs1665702791739.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Structure Editor</a><p>The Structure Editor enables you to define the contents of a main development object, including its sub objects.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bso1665702780119.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Properties Inspector</a><p>Use the Properties Inspector to view and edit the properties of the current object, or multiple objects.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532997\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532997\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Structure Worksheet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Structure Worksheet Use the Define Structure worksheet to create development objects, organize them, and set their properties. Tools Resource Browser—choose templates and other objects to create a new sub-object in the current main development object. Structure Editor—shows the main development object and its sub-objects, as well as selected properties, as a tree. You can edit properties of the selected object here, or in the Properties Inspector. Properties Inspector—shows the properties of the object selected in the Structure Editor, and enables you to edit them. How to Create a New Development Object Add Objects from the Resource Browser Rename a Development Object Edit Object Properties Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects Resize Columns Related Links Using the Uniface IDE Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy. Working with Development Objects Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same. Structure Editor The Structure Editor enables you to define the contents of a main development object, including its sub objects. Properties Inspector Use the Properties Inspector to view and edit the properties of the current object, or multiple objects. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}